To build a new react app, follow a two part process

1. Use create-react-app to generate a new project (called jsx)
   Using Dockerfile.new, and a fake server.js + package.json

# build image
docker build . -f Dockerfile.new -t myapp

# run image
docker run --name myapp -v /Users/amaheshwari/Documents/Projects/sandbox-javascript/pics:/src/pics -p 3000:8080 -d myapp

# create new app
docker exec -it myapp create-react-app pics

2. Run the new app
# build image
docker build . -f Dockerfile.app -t myapp

# run image
docker run --name myapp -v /Users/amaheshwari/Documents/Projects/sandbox-javascript/pics:/src/pics -p 3000:3000 -d myapp


3. Misc Stuff

# Get container ID
docker ps

# Print app output
docker logs myapp

# Enter the container
docker exec -it myapp /bin/bash

# Clean up
docker stop myapp; docker rm myapp
